# Trinity docs/ Directory Management

**Purpose:** Launch APO (Documentation Specialist) to organize and maintain the project's `docs/` directory with proper structure and navigation.

**Use Case:** Create organized docs/ directory structure, generate navigation README, categorize documentation files.

**Deliverable:** docs/ organization report in `trinity/reports/DOCS-ORGANIZATION-{date}.md`

---

## Overview

The `/trinity-docs` command invokes APO (Documentation Specialist) to organize the `docs/` directory. This command focuses exclusively on creating a well-structured documentation directory with proper categorization and navigation.

**APO's Responsibilities:**
- Scan existing docs/ files
- Create hierarchical directory structure (guides/, api/, architecture/, etc.)
- Generate docs/README.md navigation file
- Organize existing documentation files into categories
- Apply documentation best practices

**What This Command Does NOT Handle:**
- ❌ README.md files (use `/trinity-readme`)
- ❌ CHANGELOG.md updates (use `/trinity-changelog`)
- ❌ Root-level documentation files
- ❌ API documentation generation (use specialized tools)

---

